"""Tests for the kde.likelihood method"""
simp_kde.kde = type('kde', (object,), {})()
simp_kde.kde.samples = np.ones((2, 10))
simp_kde._obs = {'dnu': [solar_p[0], 0.1], 'numax': [solar_p[1], 0.1],
    'teff': [solar_p[-2], 0.1], 'bp_rp': [solar_p[-1], 0.1]}
simp_kde._log_obs = {x: to_log10(*simp_kde._obs[x]) for x in simp_kde._obs.
    keys() if x != 'bp_rp'}
data = np.array(solar_p.repeat(11).reshape((10, -1)))
simp_kde.kde = sm.nonparametric.KDEMultivariate(data=data, var_type=
    'cccccccccc', bw='scott')
func = simp_kde.likelihood
inp = [solar_p]
pbt.does_it_return(func, inp)
pbt.right_type(func, inp, float)
assert np.isreal(func(*inp))
assert func(*inp) < 0
